F(F(*&F5F()F&\"\"%F(F(*&F1F()F&\"\"$F(F(*&F-F()F&\"\"#F(F(*&F'F(F&F(F(
F(F(" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6-\"\"\"\"#5\"#X\"$?\"\"$5#\"$_#
F'F&F%F$F#" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 259 16 "Binomi
al Theorem" }{TEXT -1 66 " gives a formula for finding the coefficient
s of the expansion of " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^n;" "6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"
bGF&%\"nG" }{TEXT -1 10 "  for any " }{TEXT 267 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 53 ". \+
 It is relatively obvious that the coefficient of  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "a
^(n-k)*b^k;" "6#*&)%\"aG,&%\"nG\"\"\"%\"kG!\"\"F()%\"bGF)F(" }{TEXT 
-1 19 "  for any value of " }{TEXT 268 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 11 " from 0 to \+
" }{TEXT 269 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 46 " is given by the number of ways we ca
n choose " }{TEXT 270 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 8 " of the " }{TEXT 294 1 "b" }
{TEXT -1 12 "'s from the " }{TEXT 271 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 
295 1 "b" }{TEXT -1 20 "'s in the expansion " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)*(a
+b)" "6#*&,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&F&,&F%F&F'F&F&" }{TEXT -1 7 " ....( " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)" "6#,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF%" }{TEXT -1 5 " ),  " }
{TEXT 272 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 41 " times .   The number of combinations of
 " }{TEXT 273 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 18 " objects choosing " }{TEXT 274 1 "k
" }{TEXT -1 12 " at a time, " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk" "6#%$nCkG" }{TEXT 
-1 27 ", is given by the formula  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk=n!/(k!*(n-k)!)
" "6#/%$nCkG*&-%*factorialG6#%\"nG\"\"\"*&-F'6#%\"kGF*-F'6#,&F)F*F.!\"
\"F*F2" }{TEXT -1 2 " ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT 261 10 "State the " }{TEXT 260 16 "Binomial Theorem" }
{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 275 31 "and use Maple to demonstrate it" }{TEXT 
-1 1 "." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 151 "If  n is a positive integer, \+
then (a+b)^n =C(n,0)a^n*b^0+C(n,1)a^(n-1)*b^1+C(n,2)a^(n-2)*b^2+...+C(
n,n-2)a^2*b^(n-2)+C(n,n-1)a^1*b^(n-1)+C(n,n)a^0*b^n\n" }}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "expand((a+b)^4);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#,,*$)%\"aG\"\"%\"\"\"F(*(F'F()F&\"\"$F(%\"bGF(F(*(\"\"'
F()F&\"\"#F()F,F0F(F(*(F'F(F&F()F,F+F(F(*$)F,F'F(F(" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 8 "Compute " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "sum(binomial(n,k),k=0..n)" "6#
-%$sumG6$-%)binomialG6$%\"nG%\"kG/F*;\"\"!F)" }{TEXT -1 34 "  for n=1 \+
to 10.  Here the symbol " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "Sigma;" "6#%&SigmaG" }{TEXT 
-1 70 " (Greek letter Sigma) stands for sum.   (See the worksheet SumS
eq.mws)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 60 "for i from 1 to 10\ndo\ni,sum(coeff((a+1)^i,a,k),k=0.
.i);\nod;\n" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"\"\"\"#" }}{PARA 
11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"#\"\"%" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "
6$\"\"$\"\")" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"%\"#;" }}{PARA 11 
"" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"&\"#K" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"
\"'\"#k" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"(\"$G\"" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\")\"$c#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"
*\"$7&" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"#5\"%C5" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT 258 59 "What general formula do the above calculations in  sug
gest?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 28 "The general formula is 2^i.\n" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 388 
"2.  Pascal's Triangle.  Recall the definition of Pascal's Triangle.  \+
 Use Maple to construct the first 10 rows of Pascal's Triangle. (The t
rick will be to get the coefficients to occur in the correct order.  T
he Maple command for generating a sequence might be helpful. It is   s
eq(expression(i),i=m..n);   where expression(i) is an expression with \+
index i and m..n is a range of numbers." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 3 
"   " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 56 "for i from 0 to 9\nd
o\nseq(coeff((a+1)^i,a,n),n=0..i);\nod;" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"\"\"" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"\"F#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6%\"\"\"\"\"#
F#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6&\"\"\"\"\"$F$F#" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6'\"\"\"\"\"%\"\"'F$F#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
